  "prompt": "Why am I blocked from asking questions under anonymous basis on Quora?",
  "response": "There are a few potential reasons why you might be blocked from asking questions anonymously on Quora:\n\n1. **Quora's Policies**: Quora has community guidelines and policies in place to ensure the platform remains a respectful and useful space for discussion. If your previous anonymous questions violated these guidelines (e.g., spam, harassment, or inappropriate content), Quora may have restricted your ability to ask questions anonymously.\n\n2. **Account Suspension or Restrictions**: If your account has been restricted or suspended for any reason, you may lose certain privileges, including the ability to ask questions anonymously.\n\n3. **Technical Glitches**: Sometimes, technical issues or bugs on the platform can prevent certain features from working properly. This could temporarily block your ability to ask anonymous questions.\n\n4. **Abuse of Anonymity**: If you've been flagged for abusing the anonymity feature (e.g., repeatedly asking inappropriate or harmful questions), Quora may block you from using it.\n\n5. **New Account Limitations**: If you're using a new account, Quora might have additional restrictions in place to prevent misuse of features like anonymous posting.\n\nIf you believe the block was a mistake or you'd like to better understand the reason, you can reach out to Quora's support team for clarification. Be sure to review Quora's [community guidelines](https://www.quora.com/policy/community_guidelines) to ensure your questions align with their rules.",
